.TH OD 1
.SH NAME
od \- display file contents in various formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B od
[ -x | -h ] [ file ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B od
utility reads input files (or standard input if no files are specified)
and writes a formatted output of their contents. If file is - or if no filenames
are given,
.I stdin
is read.

The following options are supported:
.TP
.B \-x
Display output in hexadecimal format.
.TP
.B \-h
Display a short help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The
.B od
utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.
.SH SEE ALSO
cat(1)
